     suffix of "g," "m" or "k" will specify units of 10^9, 10^6 or 10^3
     bytes respectively.  For example:
          `-S 128K'
     Will request the remote (netserver) send and receive socket buffer
     sizes to be 128KB or 131072 bytes.

